{"type":"message","id":"cab5e280","parentId":"0f809068","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:33:56.562Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7fheya6bhjl2_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 023315\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: tic/tic_classifier.py (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action that advances the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n2. Key pending: TIC Experiment - Implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n3. The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is the current focus\r\n4. Next action requires: Implement TIC classifier, measure invariant/variant classification, predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action is to implement the Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) classifier. This is a specific, actionable task that advances Phase 1.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Read the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md doc to understand the TIC concept\r\n2. Implement a TIC classifier that can analyze pulse logs\r\n3. Start testing on the existing pulse logs\r\n\r\nLet me check if the document exists and then create an implementation plan.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the format required, I need to provide:\r\n- OBSERVATION (1-2 sentences)\r\n- ACTION (concise file edit description)\r\n- MUTATION (in triple backticks with old_text, new_text, file)\r\n\r\nFor a new file creation, old_text would be \"(new file)\".\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action: Implement a TIC classifier script that can:\r\n1. Load pulse logs\r\n2. Identify invariant vs variant patterns\r\n3. Measure classification accuracy\r\n4. Predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script for this experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY doc establishes TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) as the next critical experiment, but the actual classifier implementation hasn't been started yet. The pulse logs exist but aren't being analyzed for invariant patterns.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a TIC classifier implementation that reads pulse logs, identifies invariant vs variant structures, and tests the >70% classification accuracy threshold.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```python\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nPhase 1 Advancement: Compression-Causal Duality Experiment\r\n\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\nA compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\nSuccess Criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse content prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    \"\"\"Identifies temporal invariants across pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    INVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n        r'Phase \\d',           # Phase markers\r\n        r'GOAL|goal|Goal',     # Goal references\r\n        r'\\.md$',              # File references\r\n        r'^\\s*-\\s+\\[',         # Checkbox items\r\n        r'^\\s*###\\s+',         # Section headers\r\n    ]\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self, logs_dir: str = \"logs\"):\r\n        self.logs_dir = Path(logs_dir)\r\n        \r\n    def load_pulses(self) -> List[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Load all pulse log files sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n        pulses = []\r\n        for f in sorted(self.logs_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n            pulses.append(f.read_text())\r\n        return pulses\r\n    \r\n    def extract_features(self, text: str) -> Dict[str, any]:\r\n        \"\"\"Extract structural features from pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n        return {\r\n            'line_count': len(text.split('\\n')),\r\n            'has_phase': bool(re.search(r'Phase \\d', text)),\r\n            'has_goals': bool(re.search(r'GOAL|goal|Goal', text)),\r\n            'has_mutation': 'MUTATION' in text,\r\n            'has_observation': 'OBSERVATION' in text,\r\n            'section_count': len(re.findall(r'^\\s*###\\s+', text, re.MULTILINE)),\r\n            'checkbox_count': len(re.findall(r'^\\s*-\\s+\\[', text, re.MULTILINE)),\r\n            'word_count': len(text.split()),\r\n        }\r\n    \r\n    def is_invariant(self, features: Dict) -> bool:\r\n        \"\"\"Classify pulse content as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n        invariant_score = 0\r\n        if features['has_phase']: invariant_score += 2\r\n        if features['has_goals']: invariant_score += 2\r\n        if features['section_count'] >= 3: invariant_score += 1\r\n        if features['checkbox_count'] >= 2: invariant_score += 1\r\n        # Threshold: score >= 3 = invariant\r\n        return invariant_score >= 3\r\n    \r\n    def classify_pulses(self) -> List[Tuple[str, bool]]:\r\n        \"\"\"Classify all pulses as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n        pulses = self.load_pulses()\r\n        results = []\r\n        for pulse in pulses:\r\n            features = self.extract_features(pulse)\r\n            is_inv = self.is_invariant(features)\r\n            results.append((pulse, is_inv))\r\n        return results\r\n    \r\n    def predict_next_pulse(self, invariant_pulses: List[str]) -> str:\r\n        \"\"\"Extract common invariant structure for prediction.\"\"\"\r\n        if not invariant_pulses:\r\n            return \"\"\r\n        # Count common patterns across invariant pulses\r\n        all_features = [self.extract_features(p) for p in invariant_pulses]\r\n        avg_features = {\r\n            'line_count': sum(f['line_count'] for f in all_features) // len(all_features),\r\n            'section_count': sum(f['section_count'] for f in all_features) // len(all_features),\r\n            'checkbox_count': sum(f['checkbox_count'] for f in all_features) // len(all_features),\r\n        }\r\n        return f\"Predicted next pulse: ~{avg_features['line_count']} lines, {avg\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:33:48\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774334036561}}
